                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-13T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1928—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 13—12:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. My 48, March 13, 1 p.m. Am confidentially informed, by reliable authority
                    speaking unofficially, meeting of March 30 will accept general terms of last
                    Austrian offer for settlement of European relief debts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Houghton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
